r/actions/runs/24250536747))","episodeId":"ep_ci_failure_001","source":"ci_failure","content":"Task: -Engine-Tester/actions/runs/24250536747)) | Outcome: failed | Observation: The pipeline completed all stages except ship, which failed on git push due to stale remote state — another process updated main while this pipeline was running. The verify stage completed after 1 retry but produced typecheck errors in the report, suggesting the retry may have passed without properly resolving the underlying TypeScript type mismatches in PagesPageConfig validation. | Failed at: ship | Suggestion: Add a `git fetch origin main` step before the ship stage's force-push to ensure the local ref is up-to-date with remote, and investigate whether the verify stage's retry logic is properly re-running type checks rather than passing cached results. | Flaw: ship — Git push rejected due to stale remote ref — no fetch/update before push | Stages: taskify:completed, plan:completed, build:completed, verify:completed, review:completed, review-fix:completed, ship:failed","createdAt":"2026-04-10T16:17:53.227Z","wordCount":963,"positions":[0,7,14,21,29,34,50,59,68,85,94,108,115,122,134,144,148,153,160,166,173,181,189,197,205,210,221,234,247,254,260,270,278,288,297,307,321,329,344,359,366,374,383,397,408,419,424,438,454,468,479,486,498,505,509,515,522,528,533,544,549,557,563,571,582,588,595,601,611,623,635,647,654,662,668,677,686,689,697,702,709,716,721,729,736,747,753,760,764,769,778,785,791,798,804,807,813,820,827,834,842,850,861,866,877,883,894,901,912,919,930,937,941,952,957]},"ep_stage_diary_001":{"taskId":"approve`","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_001","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"build\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"When adding a new module in src/utils/, follow the established co-located test pattern: src/utils/<name>.test.ts next to src/utils/<name>.ts, matching existing files like retry.test.ts and result.test\",\"scope\":\"src/utils\"},{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"Kody's clarifying questions about config fields and rules went unanswered, blocking the implementation — product answers must precede code generation.\",\"scope\":\"configValidator\"},{\"kind\":\"decision\",\"text\":\"Use TDD: write the test file first (red), then implement the module (green), per project acceptance criteria for new utilities.\",\"scope\":\"src/utils\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T17:04:16.056Z","wordCount":659,"positions":[2,10,18,31,38,47,59,68,72,82,86,94,105,117,120,128,133,142,146,153,159,164,167,175,179,186,192,196,205,214,220,225,231,236,243,250,257,265,269,279,286,295,302,309,320,330,336,343,354,360,365,377,390,407,415,423,428,436,441,455,463,483,490,501,508,512,517,527,532,537,544,555,569,577,585,589,597,608,621,625,638,646,650]},"ep_stage_diary_002":{"taskId":"approve`","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_002","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"buildTargets validation only checks for Array type, not that elements are strings — {buildTargets: [42]} would pass validation\",\"scope\":\"src/utils/configValidator.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Use Result<T, E> type from src/utils/result.ts for fallible operations instead of throwing\",\"scope\":\"src/utils\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Vitest tests are co-located next to source files using .test.ts suffix (e.g., retry.test.ts, result.test.ts)\",\"scope\":\"testing\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"TypeScript type errors are caught at build step, not just at runtime — validating element types of arrays is a distinct concern from array type itself\",\"scope\":\"src/utils/configValidator.ts\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T17:07:18.061Z","wordCount":741,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,48,55,68,79,84,95,101,107,116,129,140,155,166,171,184,192,196,202,218,225,232,245,252,256,269,279,283,289,296,303,312,323,334,345,353,357,367,374,387,394,401,411,414,422,430,437,443,450,455,458,472,478,483,487,494,499,505,513,525,532,